WEBVTT

00:42.500 --> 00:46.004
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05.148 --> 01:08.276
Ms. Dam Ye-jin, what are you doing?
Didn't you hear the car?

01:22.040 --> 01:27.587
Are you okay? Ye-jin, by any chance,
are you drunk?

01:38.556 --> 01:39.390
Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

02:08.837 --> 02:10.004
Wait here for a second.

02:21.057 --> 02:21.891
Thank you.

05:21.696 --> 05:22.572
Dam Ye…

05:38.338 --> 05:39.172
Huh?

05:41.132 --> 05:41.966
Mechoori.

05:49.015 --> 05:49.932
What are you--

06:09.535 --> 06:10.495
It smells good.

06:17.126 --> 06:19.337
What cologne do you wear?

06:19.921 --> 06:21.756
Just what do you think you're doing?

06:27.345 --> 06:30.598
What a light, nice, woody, and
musky scent. I think our customers

06:30.681 --> 06:34.519
would really like this as well.

06:37.021 --> 06:38.231
I'm not wearing cologne.

06:44.946 --> 06:46.489
You just want it for yourself.

06:51.369 --> 06:52.453
You're so annoying.

06:55.998 --> 06:58.251
That little… Dam Ye--

09:07.171 --> 09:08.256
It's empty.

09:17.765 --> 09:19.058
How did that happen?

09:21.477 --> 09:22.311
It hurts.

10:19.702 --> 10:20.536
Mom.

10:22.872 --> 10:25.833
Pick up. Please pick up.

11:18.678 --> 11:19.679
Mechoori!

11:23.391 --> 11:26.435
Som, shouldn't you be at school?
Is something wrong?

11:26.936 --> 11:32.817
Well, I mean, not exactly. Do you
have any money?

11:34.402 --> 11:35.277
How much money?

11:35.361 --> 11:37.738
Well, my sister promised me
fifty-thousand won if I help clean

11:37.822 --> 11:39.323
the store next week.

11:40.533 --> 11:44.036
You want to borrow it? Oh, Som-yi,
what are you up to now? Huh?

11:44.120 --> 11:45.204
It's poca.

11:47.832 --> 11:48.749
What was that?

11:52.002 --> 11:55.715
Poker? You-- You can't do that.

11:55.798 --> 11:57.800
Why not? But it's my only joy in life.

11:57.883 --> 11:58.884
Na Som!

11:59.802 --> 12:03.305
Listen, there are plenty of other fun
activities, because once you get

12:03.389 --> 12:06.767
addicted, it can be hard to break free,
all right? No gambling.

12:08.144 --> 12:09.019
What do you mean?

12:12.356 --> 12:14.734
A photo card! Poca! I need one!

12:15.526 --> 12:16.610
A photo card?

12:20.281 --> 12:23.451
A photo card. Fifty thousand?

12:26.537 --> 12:29.874
Mechoori, you should take the day
off to go online and learn about

12:29.957 --> 12:31.500
the modern world.

12:32.376 --> 12:33.586
DAM YE-JIN

12:37.548 --> 12:39.425
Mechoori, are you stanning her?

12:39.508 --> 12:40.342
No.

12:41.343 --> 12:42.553
What's stanning mean?

12:42.636 --> 12:43.637
Do you like her, I mean?

12:43.721 --> 12:44.555
No way!

12:46.223 --> 12:49.185
It's just, something about her
is bothering me.

12:50.060 --> 12:52.563
That's exactly how stanning starts.

12:54.023 --> 12:55.608
Som-yi, want something to eat?

13:07.828 --> 13:09.914
Oh, jeez. My sister's in trouble.

13:10.414 --> 13:11.499
Hmm?

13:13.083 --> 13:16.670
Oh, nothing. At least nothing happened to
her overnight.

13:18.047 --> 13:20.049
-How do you know that?
-She's streaming right now.

13:20.132 --> 13:21.842
-Streaming?
-Live streaming, look.

13:22.885 --> 13:25.763
Hi, everyone. Good morning. You guys,
check out this sky. Isn't it amazing?

13:25.846 --> 13:28.849
So, this is my favorite spot along the
Han River. Because whenever I come here,

13:28.933 --> 13:31.644
I feel so free. I figured it was too cool
to keep to myself. Also, this

13:31.727 --> 13:34.396
doesn't even capture a fraction of
its beauty. The weather today? It's

13:34.480 --> 13:40.694
already getting hot. I recommend dressing
lightly.

13:45.950 --> 13:49.078
Aren't you curious to know whether
she slept well, or…

13:49.161 --> 13:50.412
Oh, my God. Do you see that?

13:50.496 --> 13:51.872
If she missed a meal?

13:52.456 --> 13:54.375
I told you, it's nothing like that.

13:54.458 --> 13:56.293
Hey, somebody's touchy.

14:01.674 --> 14:04.885
I think you might've gotten my
measurements wrong last time. The waist

14:04.969 --> 14:08.180
-is too tight.
-All I did was hang it up.

14:10.307 --> 14:11.934
You sure you haven't gained weight?

14:12.017 --> 14:15.479
Hey, come on. You know I count my
calories before I go on air. What's

14:15.563 --> 14:16.689
going on?

14:22.778 --> 14:26.448
I didn't make you very much. How about
potatoes? I grew these myself. Wash it

14:26.532 --> 14:29.451
down with some sikhye.

14:37.126 --> 14:38.502
But I barely had any.

14:38.586 --> 14:40.212
I swear, it only shows up on Saturdays.

14:40.296 --> 14:42.381
That's ridiculous. Seriously. Oh, go
bother someone else.

14:42.464 --> 14:44.174
No, I swear. I swear to God. I really--

14:44.258 --> 14:47.761
Oh, I'm loving your outfit. Is it a
little tight?

14:50.180 --> 14:52.016
-No, it isn't. Oh, about the shoes.
-Yes, it is.

14:52.099 --> 14:55.311
I want to change to ones that cover my
feet.

14:55.936 --> 14:56.770
Here you go.

14:56.854 --> 14:57.855
What happened to your feet?

14:57.938 --> 14:58.939
Did you get hurt?

14:59.023 --> 15:02.985
Uh, I don't know. I just woke up
like this. I must've cut them somewhere.

15:03.068 --> 15:05.571
How could you have cut them while you
were sleeping? You okay?

15:05.654 --> 15:08.866
The only problem is I've been eating too
well, so don't worry.

15:08.949 --> 15:11.577
Anyway, what were you two giggling about
before?

15:11.660 --> 15:12.786
Oh, well the thing is…

15:13.537 --> 15:14.413
Ms. Dam!

15:14.496 --> 15:15.331
You scared me.

15:15.831 --> 15:16.999
Do you have something?

15:17.082 --> 15:19.960
It's not just something. It's big news.
I asked them to secure as much room

15:20.044 --> 15:22.463
as possible in the warehouse for
the essence, and they went and

15:22.546 --> 15:25.424
cleared out an entire warehouse for it.

15:25.925 --> 15:28.135
Really, an entire warehouse? All of it?

15:28.218 --> 15:31.180
The thought of cramming that warehouse
with our essence is giving me a rush of

15:31.263 --> 15:32.306
dopamine.

15:32.389 --> 15:33.223
Dopamine.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.185
So, will you be setting new records for
the highest sales in the shortest

15:36.268 --> 15:37.519
amount of time ever?

15:38.020 --> 15:39.313
Yes, we will!

15:39.939 --> 15:41.690
Things are going well with Gojeuneok,
right?

15:41.774 --> 15:44.526
Oh, why even ask that? Don't you
know Ye-jin? So, tell Mr. Seo to get us

15:44.610 --> 15:49.073
all the essence he can and we'll sell
them all for him.

15:49.156 --> 15:50.282
Sell all of 'em!

16:06.215 --> 16:08.968
A LARGE WAREHOUSE
WHICH HAS BEEN COMPLETELY CLEARED OUT

16:13.222 --> 16:16.809
Mechoori! Uh, no, no, no. Matthew
Lee, can you please just help me this

16:16.892 --> 16:20.604
once? I'm in big trouble. Oh, Mr. Lee,
please. Just this once, help me. I

16:20.688 --> 16:26.694
won't ask you for anything ever again.
If you'd show mercy, I'll…

16:32.199 --> 16:34.243
Ba-bawk. Bawk.

16:35.452 --> 16:38.664
Mechoori, no, I mean, Matthew Lee.
Please save my life just this

16:49.883 --> 16:53.804
This is scaring me now. Ah, I take it
back. I'm sorry. I take back what I said

16:54.805 --> 16:56.265
-about you scaring me.
-Bawk.

17:02.271 --> 17:03.105
Bawk, bawk…

17:03.188 --> 17:06.066
FROM NOW ON, YOU WILL NEVER
GET TO SEE THE MUSHROOMS.

17:08.318 --> 17:09.486
Mr. Lee!

17:11.905 --> 17:13.365
Of course, I'm Dam Ye-jin!

17:13.449 --> 17:16.910
Well, then don't worry about it.
Let's secure as many as we can.

17:16.994 --> 17:19.913
Go for it, I've got your back. Do you
understand, Ye-jin?!

17:21.999 --> 17:24.585
Our team is unstoppable.

17:27.087 --> 17:28.464
I have a meeting to get to.

17:36.305 --> 17:39.975
Granny, what's my sister supposed to
do now? Someone will snatch Mechoori

17:40.059 --> 17:41.810
away from her.

17:43.187 --> 17:45.105
What's so bad about Jin-yi?

17:45.189 --> 17:48.400
Oh, my poor sister doesn't stand a
chance.

17:48.484 --> 17:50.486
It's what's inside that matters.

17:51.278 --> 17:55.157
Then between my sister and Dam Ye-jin,
Granny. Who do you think is prettier?

17:56.408 --> 17:57.868
-Jin.
-Really?

17:58.368 --> 18:02.331
Dam Ye-jin. She has such a bright smile.

18:02.414 --> 18:03.874
Granny, come on.

18:09.713 --> 18:13.008
-Hello, sweetie. Mechoori?
-Mechoori?

18:14.176 --> 18:16.887
Who even are you? Why are you
asking about him?

18:16.970 --> 18:19.389
I'm Dam Ye-jin. Who are you?

18:22.184 --> 18:26.772
None of your business. But, hey, are you
close with our Mechoori?

18:26.855 --> 18:29.108
Our Mechoori? Are you close with him?

18:29.608 --> 18:31.235
Yeah, we are very close.

18:32.486 --> 18:35.906
Really? Then I bet you know where he is
right now, don't you?

18:36.448 --> 18:37.825
Why do you wanna know?

18:37.908 --> 18:39.701
Because I'm on my way to see him now.

18:39.785 --> 18:41.829
Mechoori's too busy. He's harvesting
corn today.

18:41.912 --> 18:43.413
Corn, yeah? What time is that?

18:45.791 --> 18:48.585
Oh, I guess you wouldn't know that,
would you?

18:48.669 --> 18:51.255
Come on. There isn't one single
thing about Mechoori's schedule that

18:51.338 --> 18:52.965
I don't know.

18:53.841 --> 18:56.301
Really? Then let's go over the details in
person.

18:59.304 --> 19:00.139
What the heck?

19:02.099 --> 19:04.184
-Ah!
-She just hung up, Granny.

19:14.027 --> 19:16.113
You're the home shopping host,
Dam Ye-jin?

19:16.196 --> 19:19.449
So it was you. Hi. That mask you have,
where did you buy it? It looks

19:19.533 --> 19:23.203
really soft and confortable.

19:24.496 --> 19:26.623
-Well, I didn't buy it.
-Really?

19:29.126 --> 19:31.587
By the way, shouldn't you be at school
right now?

19:31.670 --> 19:36.466
I'm getting a lesson on life from Granny.
Gaining experience from my senior.

19:37.926 --> 19:39.678
What about this kind of experience?

19:41.096 --> 19:43.432
DEOKPUNG CORNFIELD
SUPER SWEET CORN

19:43.515 --> 19:44.725
We'll be starting the exercise now.
Dada-dada-dun. Dada-dada-dun.

19:44.808 --> 19:48.520
Dada-dada-dun, dada-dun. Hurry up,
get over here!

19:49.396 --> 19:52.858
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven,
eight.

19:52.941 --> 19:53.775
Six!

19:54.276 --> 19:55.110
Look over there!

19:55.194 --> 20:00.574
Two, two, three, four. You can
look later. Now, get back to it.

20:01.617 --> 20:03.744
Okay, okay, the knees. The knees,
the knees.

20:03.827 --> 20:04.703
Okay.

20:05.204 --> 20:08.790
There you go. Good. Keep it up,

20:09.291 --> 20:13.503
-keep it up. Full circles. One, two,
-Full circles. One, two, three, four,

20:13.587 --> 20:17.341
-three, four. Switch. Five, six,
-five, six, seven-- Nine, ten, eleven--

20:17.424 --> 20:19.927
-Na Som, no school?
-seven, eight, nine, ten, eleven, twelve.

20:20.010 --> 20:21.428
I guess not.

20:21.511 --> 20:22.346
What do you want?

20:22.429 --> 20:25.265
Oh, right, uh-- Mr. Lee. Well, it's been
a while, right?

20:28.435 --> 20:30.312
-Wow.
-There they go.

20:32.981 --> 20:36.568
It's not what you think. I can
assure you, I didn't come here to bother

20:36.652 --> 20:40.030
you. Uh, Ms. Yang said she'd be
harvesting corn, so I thought I'd lend

20:40.113 --> 20:41.114
a hand.

20:42.699 --> 20:45.869
-You want to harvest corn with us?
-Yes. I may not look that handy, but I am.

20:45.953 --> 20:48.080
No, thank you. We have enough people.

20:48.163 --> 20:48.997
Come on.

20:49.623 --> 20:52.042
Once you see me working, I think
you'll like it.

20:53.794 --> 20:56.797
I think you'll like it. I think
you'll like it. I think you'll like it.

20:56.880 --> 20:57.714
It smells good.

21:00.259 --> 21:03.512
Oh my God, are you okay? You should
take better care of yourself,

21:03.595 --> 21:05.681
especially at a time like this.

21:06.765 --> 21:09.851
You're one to talk. You should
take better care of yourself.

21:11.144 --> 21:12.896
-Huh?
-Oh, well--

21:12.980 --> 21:15.440
Mechoori! They're all waiting for you!

21:15.524 --> 21:16.358
Goodness.

21:16.942 --> 21:20.779
Okay, those of you who are ready,
let's start heading up there.

21:21.280 --> 21:24.825
What's wrong with this guy? Wait for me!

21:25.909 --> 21:27.786
HARVESTING BEGINS

21:27.869 --> 21:29.871
Okay, trim this just right.

21:32.249 --> 21:35.836
That's right. There we go. Nice cut.
Uh, yeah. There you go. Let me get

21:35.919 --> 21:37.170
some here.

21:40.382 --> 21:45.220
Everyone, pick them properly so my
son-in-law's business can really thrive!

21:45.304 --> 21:46.972
-We will!
-That's right.

21:47.055 --> 21:48.598
Don't you worry about a thing!

21:48.682 --> 21:51.351
We're in luck, my son-in-law's
makgeolli is going to be a hit. This is

21:51.435 --> 21:52.269
some great corn.

21:52.352 --> 21:53.937
To the makgeolli's big success!

21:54.438 --> 21:55.522
Makgeolli!

21:55.605 --> 21:59.234
To the makgeolli's success! To the
makgeolli's success!

22:01.611 --> 22:02.863
Come on, come on. Got it.

22:04.865 --> 22:07.659
Wow. No way, this one's huge.

22:18.086 --> 22:25.010
God, it's so hot. I'm exhausted. Ah, this
heat, I feel like I'm gonna die.

22:27.721 --> 22:33.268
I can't do any more. I feel like I might
actually die. I'm so exhausted.

22:50.535 --> 22:54.247
I can do this. Ah, I can do this if
I try.

23:15.227 --> 23:16.269
Time for snack break.

23:16.353 --> 23:18.855
-All right, let's go have some snacks.
-Snack time already?

23:18.939 --> 23:20.565
Come on, snacks.

23:21.066 --> 23:22.025
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

23:22.526 --> 23:23.485
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

23:23.985 --> 23:25.404
Okay. Eat up, everyone!

23:25.487 --> 23:27.114
Okay, cheers. This looks great.

23:27.197 --> 23:29.866
-Eat up! Okay, cheers! Cheers!
-Wow. This is so good.

23:29.950 --> 23:30.784
Cheers!

23:32.494 --> 23:33.912
Hey, make me a bowl.

23:35.038 --> 23:37.124
Ah, what is this?

23:38.750 --> 23:40.377
Oh, that is so refreshing.

23:40.460 --> 23:41.837
Sweetie, aren't you eating?

23:41.920 --> 23:43.463
No, I shouldn't. I have to lose weight.

23:43.547 --> 23:47.467
Oh, come on. Snack time is to help
you stay alive. So eat.

23:47.551 --> 23:49.386
It's really okay. I'm not that much
of an eater.

23:49.469 --> 23:50.804
Oh, come on.

23:51.471 --> 23:53.640
-Come on. Just have one.
-It's really okay.

23:57.185 --> 24:00.147
Yeah, I'll take another one. You'll be
fine. Tasty food doesn't have calories.

24:00.230 --> 24:01.565
Yeah, that's right. Here.

24:05.360 --> 24:06.194
Hey, eat up!

24:17.664 --> 24:19.458
Woah! It's so good!

24:19.541 --> 24:20.667
BEAUTIFUL FLAVOR

24:32.304 --> 24:35.223
I ate so well. Oh my God! If only we
had some iced americanos to wash all of

24:35.307 --> 24:38.018
this down, am I right?

24:39.102 --> 24:39.936
Yeah.

24:40.520 --> 24:42.355
How about some iced coffee everyone?

24:42.856 --> 24:45.692
-Oh, Jin!
-Jin, you made it! You're here!

24:46.318 --> 24:47.152
Who is that?

24:47.235 --> 24:50.572
She's Deokpung's very own mascot. We
couldn't live without Jin-yi.

24:51.281 --> 24:53.909
This, this, this. And this. It all

24:53.992 --> 24:56.536
-came from Jin-yi's shop. Even these.
-These as well.

24:56.620 --> 24:57.579
Oh, my.

24:59.956 --> 25:00.790
Okay.

25:03.502 --> 25:04.336
Ta-da!

25:05.337 --> 25:11.009
Wow, looks refreshing. Here you go.
Take this, take it. Yeah, coffee's here.

25:11.092 --> 25:13.803
That's my sister. Isn't she pretty?
She's got a great personality, too.

25:13.887 --> 25:15.597
-Coffee's here.
-Oh, coffee. Delicious.

25:15.680 --> 25:17.432
-Thank you.
-Here, have some coffee.

25:17.516 --> 25:19.518
-Hey, Na Som-yi, what are you doing here?
-I take back that last part.

25:19.601 --> 25:21.311
-Oh, it's so hot.
-Ugh, you little…

25:21.394 --> 25:25.232
-It's to hot.
-Ae-ra. You want to sit next to me?

25:28.109 --> 25:31.446
So adorable. She never says yes to me.
Not even once.

25:31.530 --> 25:32.989
Kwang-mo, are you still hitting on her?

25:33.073 --> 25:35.158
I mean, I wouldn't say yes to you either.

25:37.118 --> 25:39.496
You know we're harvesting the super
sweet corn today.

25:39.579 --> 25:41.665
I already said I won't buy unless
it's at my price.

25:41.748 --> 25:43.833
How do you expect us to sell at
half price?

25:43.917 --> 25:45.335
Well then, it's my final offer.

25:45.418 --> 25:48.922
We turned down all the department
stores' offers so we'd be able to

25:49.005 --> 25:52.259
supply it to your brewery. You're
putting me in a tough spot. I'll

25:52.342 --> 25:56.680
terminate your contract after charging
you the stated penalty fee.

26:00.058 --> 26:00.892
Mechoori.

26:02.018 --> 26:03.895
Oh, sir. Um, what are--

26:03.979 --> 26:07.566
Could you please cut me some slack?
My sales are dropping day by day.

26:07.649 --> 26:10.360
All of my employees are leaving.

26:12.571 --> 26:16.324
Things have gotten so bad that I'm doing
deliveries myself. The truth is, I

26:16.408 --> 26:19.411
offered half knowing that you'd refuse.

26:22.622 --> 26:25.709
Is Ms. Yang aware you've been struggling?

26:26.251 --> 26:29.045
Please keep it secret from my
mother-in-law.

26:32.090 --> 26:35.218
My son-in-law said he won't be buying the
corn, after all?

26:35.719 --> 26:38.972
Yes. He's developing a new product,
so I'll be selling it to some other

26:39.055 --> 26:39.889
buyer.

26:39.973 --> 26:43.310
Why, when this corn is so good? Then what
will you do with it all?

26:44.644 --> 26:47.814
It'll be okay. I just have to
find somebody quickly. Let's call

26:47.897 --> 26:50.984
it a day. Thank you all for your hard
work.

26:51.067 --> 26:54.446
I mean, if it's not harvested by
the day after tomorrow, it's going to

26:54.529 --> 26:55.822
lose all the flavor.

26:55.905 --> 26:58.658
-It's true.
-Oh, my head. My head.

26:59.242 --> 27:00.952
Ma'am, let me take you home. Okay.

27:01.036 --> 27:04.164
Oh, I'm not going anywhere until I'm done
harvesting it all.

27:04.247 --> 27:08.335
Wait, ma'am. We have nowhere to store it
anyhow. It's better off left as it is.

27:08.418 --> 27:11.254
Go home and rest. I'll come up with
something.

27:21.556 --> 27:22.766
All this for nothing.

27:26.102 --> 27:29.105
I know, I know. It's really going to
spoil, don't you think?

27:36.404 --> 27:41.034
So it seems like all this corn has
turned into a real headache, hasn't it?

27:42.327 --> 27:45.747
You should go home now as well. Thank you
for helping me out.

27:46.247 --> 27:48.583
I'm just trying to help find a solution.

27:48.667 --> 27:51.544
We'll be all right. I can just
find another buyer.

27:51.628 --> 27:55.465
This produce is about to go bad.
You don't want this to go to waste…

27:55.548 --> 27:58.301
This really has nothing to do with
you, Dam Ye-jin.

27:58.885 --> 28:02.305
I also helped out and almost got a heat
stroke. How do you expect me to

28:02.389 --> 28:05.767
just leave when all of our hard work
is about to be wasted? I don't

28:05.850 --> 28:07.519
think I can.

28:14.609 --> 28:15.443
Let's sell it.

28:16.820 --> 28:17.654
What

28:17.737 --> 28:19.864
Let's use my livestream to sell
this corn.

28:21.700 --> 28:22.742
But why would you do that?

28:22.826 --> 28:26.329
They call me 'field expert' because I'm
a host who works on location.

28:27.038 --> 28:27.872
So what?

28:27.956 --> 28:31.000
So, I understand this must be
quite surreal for you, but this is

28:31.084 --> 28:33.169
an amazing offer.

28:38.091 --> 28:40.593
Are you not confident in the quality
of your corn?

28:45.765 --> 28:48.393
BRIX: UNIT THAT MEASURES THE SUGAR
CONTENT OF FRUITS

28:49.436 --> 28:52.230
It a hundred times more likely to be
infested by bugs.

28:52.313 --> 28:54.149
But I only used natural fertilizers.

28:55.233 --> 28:58.820
Right. That's why the top home
shopping host has decided to bet on it.

28:58.903 --> 29:01.197
Mechoori, please round everyone up again.

29:05.827 --> 29:08.955
Hi, Mr. Hwang. Can you transfer me to the
online department?

29:10.707 --> 29:13.501
-Oh, okay, coming. Coming.
-Uh, hold-- Hold right there.

29:13.585 --> 29:14.419
Here?

29:14.502 --> 29:15.336
That's perfect.

29:19.340 --> 29:22.719
DAM YE-JIN'S FIRST LIVE COMMERCE:
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE SUPER SWEET CORN

29:24.763 --> 29:28.558
You two, please remain in the field,
and when the camera moves in, just grab

29:28.641 --> 29:30.435
a juicy one and eat it right away.

29:30.518 --> 29:31.644
-Okay.
-Okay.

29:31.728 --> 29:34.606
All right, please feel free to cook
whatever you want with the corn.

29:34.689 --> 29:35.523
Okay.

29:35.607 --> 29:37.484
-All right.
-All right. Thanks again.

29:39.694 --> 29:44.032
You're an incredible director. Can you
zoom in tight on me when I eat the corn?

29:44.532 --> 29:48.244
Oh, come on. I'm not gonna miss a single
shot, so do whatever you want to.

29:51.247 --> 29:54.667
I found a warehouse that can
store and ship three-thousand containers.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.128
Three-thousand. Okay, Give me ten
more minutes.

29:57.212 --> 30:00.340
Wait, hold on a moment. Ms. Dam. Are you
going to be wearing that for the show?

30:00.423 --> 30:03.551
I mean, this will be aired nationwide.

30:04.344 --> 30:07.180
I think this is the perfect for promoting
super sweet corn.

30:07.263 --> 30:08.181
Sounds good to me.

30:12.143 --> 30:13.853
Here we go! Here we go!

30:16.981 --> 30:17.899
Oh, look at that!

30:18.691 --> 30:22.070
It's live! We can start our show now!

30:27.158 --> 30:30.453
-Ten more minutes.
-Right. Let's get ready.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.042
DEOKPUNG COMMUNITY CENTER

30:36.125 --> 30:41.297
Hurry, hurry! Hurry, hurry, hurry!
There's no time to waste.

30:47.887 --> 30:51.307
LIMITED SALE FOR TODAY ONLY!
DAM YE-JIN'S FIRST LIVESTREAM SHOPPING

30:53.768 --> 30:56.563
You came running just to show me
this? Like some gotcha moment?

30:56.646 --> 30:59.232
I came because she went from trying to
protect her slot to hosting a

30:59.315 --> 31:03.152
live event, all of a sudden. She's
selling corn.

31:05.321 --> 31:08.867
Despite what happened five years ago,
she's right on your heels now.

31:08.950 --> 31:12.871
Ma'am. Dam Ye-jin's the name and face
of HIT, which makes this a matter of

31:12.954 --> 31:14.831
HIT's prestige.

31:16.916 --> 31:19.544
Really? Selling quality products at
reasonable prices. I think that's

31:19.627 --> 31:24.924
prestigious enough for a home
shopping host.

31:25.008 --> 31:27.844
You're really just gonna let her
run wild, doing whatever it is she wants?

31:27.927 --> 31:29.387
I only have one standard.

31:30.013 --> 31:33.933
Survival. Yun-ji, you should get off your
high horse, and start thinking about

31:34.017 --> 31:35.768
your own plan.

31:38.938 --> 31:42.317
SUPER SWEET STEAMED CORN, RAW CORN
NATIONWIDE DELIVERY AVAILABLE

31:42.400 --> 31:45.361
You curious what I'm doing way out here?

31:45.904 --> 31:49.365
Today I'm offering, straight from
Dockpun, super, super, super, super

31:49.449 --> 31:53.161
sweet corn. Ten ears per box, for a total
of three thousand. We're limited

31:53.244 --> 31:56.831
to only three thousand boxes!

32:00.084 --> 32:03.713
We'll be shipping them fast and fresh,
straight from Deokpung Village to

32:03.796 --> 32:08.134
your home. So everyone, place those
orders.

32:08.718 --> 32:11.930
The farmers are working super hard
to harvest the corn. Let's go

32:12.013 --> 32:14.307
have a word with them. Good afternoon.

32:14.807 --> 32:16.392
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

32:16.476 --> 32:18.519
Okay, guys. Show us the corn
you've grown.

32:18.603 --> 32:19.479
Oh, the corn?

32:19.562 --> 32:20.438
Yes.

32:20.521 --> 32:21.356
Ah, right.

32:23.024 --> 32:26.945
We didn't use any pesticides here, so
you can just eat 'em raw.

32:27.028 --> 32:29.948
I'd like to recite a poem about the corn.
Totally delicious.

32:30.031 --> 32:30.865
Go ahead.

32:31.366 --> 32:33.368
-Delicious!
-Juicy kernels. Super sweet corn!

32:33.451 --> 32:34.285
Juicy!

32:36.245 --> 32:37.080
Damn fool.

32:37.163 --> 32:40.083
Wow, look at this great cob, crammed full
of kernels. It's almost as big as

32:40.166 --> 32:44.253
-my forearm. Just huge, don't you agree?
-Come on. Don't make us look like idiots!

32:44.337 --> 32:47.674
It's completely delicious as it is, but,
there are other ways to enjoy it

32:47.757 --> 32:49.550
as well. Let's go take a look.

32:50.051 --> 32:52.553
Hello. What's this?

32:53.137 --> 32:55.807
This is a delicious super sweet corn
pancake!

32:55.890 --> 32:57.016
Corn pancake.

32:57.809 --> 33:00.395
And over here's corn salad!

33:01.145 --> 33:04.607
If anyone's concerned because you
can't cook, don't worry. It's still

33:04.691 --> 33:06.401
amazing even if you eat it raw.

33:08.903 --> 33:12.448
It really is so sweet, it's like fruit.
Mr. Director, have some.

33:15.159 --> 33:19.872
It sold out. It sold out! It sold out!

33:22.083 --> 33:25.503
Thank you all very much for your love
and support. Though this was a

33:25.586 --> 33:29.590
surprise live stream. I'll see you again
tomorrow night on "It's a HIT", back on

33:29.674 --> 33:33.594
primetime. Thank you again for all your
love. This is Dam Ye-jin, signing off.

33:33.678 --> 33:34.721
Bye, everyone!

33:35.221 --> 33:36.264
And cut!

33:40.309 --> 33:41.519
Ah, oh my god!

33:42.687 --> 33:44.105
We sold out!

33:45.523 --> 33:49.902
Oh, heavens above! God, the Buddha,
thank you! Oh, my god!

33:51.320 --> 33:53.698
Sweetie, you're my granddaughter now!

33:53.781 --> 33:56.242
Oh, it's all because the product's so
good.

33:56.325 --> 33:58.703
Are you sure it's not because you're so
pretty?

33:59.579 --> 34:02.415
Gather round. Gather round. Let's take
a picture. Ready?

34:05.918 --> 34:10.339
Mechoori! When are we gonna pick up
the rest of this and pack it up?

34:11.007 --> 34:11.841
Let's do it right now.

34:11.924 --> 34:14.427
Okay, I'll round up everyone who's just
hanging around.

34:14.510 --> 34:15.344
Oh, I'll help too.

34:15.428 --> 34:18.264
Ugh, you don't even have friends.
Go to the field and start picking corn.

34:18.347 --> 34:19.182
Oh, jeez.

34:21.684 --> 34:22.518
Honey!

34:25.605 --> 34:26.439
Dam Ye-jin.

34:30.401 --> 34:33.613
Dam Ye-jin. Are you awake?

34:35.406 --> 34:36.240
Huh?

34:41.079 --> 34:42.205
Mechoori?

34:44.707 --> 34:50.338
Dam Ye-jin. Do you recognize me? Do you
recognize me or not?

34:51.756 --> 34:55.468
God, this is really bad. Dam Ye-jin.
Dam Ye-jin! Please, can you hear me?!

34:55.551 --> 34:58.012
Dam Ye-jin! Dam Ye--

35:03.392 --> 35:04.352
Woah, woah.

35:07.522 --> 35:09.273
Dam Ye-jin. Talk to me.

35:12.026 --> 35:16.572
Am I in a hospital? No way, I've never
fainted before.

35:17.406 --> 35:18.241
Oh, okay.

35:19.117 --> 35:23.079
Did I get carried here like the female
protagonist in a romance movie?

35:24.539 --> 35:25.456
Uh, well…

35:27.959 --> 35:30.336
I thought this only happened in
the movies, but it was real. I

35:30.419 --> 35:33.381
always thought it was just fantasy. I
thought they were hamming it up a bit to

35:33.464 --> 35:38.928
much. It was all real. Is this real
life or…

35:46.144 --> 35:48.813
Hey, Muk. I don't think she's in her
right mind.

35:49.397 --> 35:52.733
-This feels way too familiar. It's real.
-It's like she's possessed.

35:52.817 --> 35:56.904
Hey, is she terminally ill, or what? Muk,
get over here. Muk!

35:56.988 --> 36:00.074
It's only heatstroke. People don't
die that easily.

36:04.203 --> 36:05.997
So this is what it feels like.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.666
WOORI DEOKPUNG MEDICAL CLINIC

36:08.749 --> 36:12.211
It's heatstroke. No, I'm saying she
was just overheated. Yeah, she'll

36:12.295 --> 36:16.007
be fine soon enough. But who is she?
It's not like you to ask for a favor,

36:16.090 --> 36:17.216
you know.

36:20.845 --> 36:23.639
No one. Okay. Take care.

36:32.940 --> 36:34.692
Mechoori, you're here. How are you?

36:39.614 --> 36:40.615
What is this?

36:45.828 --> 36:49.248
Hey, why are you giving me so much?
I said I'd charge half price for

36:49.332 --> 36:51.626
the storage unit. I-- I can't take
all this.

36:52.251 --> 36:55.796
I'm only trying to address the source of
Ms. Yang's headaches. And your

36:55.880 --> 36:59.550
makgeolli's basically medicine for
the elders of Deokpung Village. It'd be

36:59.634 --> 37:02.595
terrible to lose it. Please don't
forget to eat your meals.

37:05.514 --> 37:06.349
Mechoori.

37:06.432 --> 37:08.392
DEOKPUNG SUPER SWEET CORN
MAKGEOLLI BREWERY

37:08.476 --> 37:13.814
Oh, my little mechoori, you're so sweet.
Now, let's get you inside so you can

37:15.024 --> 37:17.068
DEOKPUNG ANIMAL HOSPITAL

37:17.151 --> 37:19.612
-Sleep tight. There you go. All right.
-Hey, Dad!

37:20.196 --> 37:25.076
Oh, hi. Hey, how'd it go? Is she okay?
So, did she wake up yet? How is she?

37:25.159 --> 37:28.079
It's heatstroke.
So is she Mechoori's girlfriend, then?

37:28.579 --> 37:33.292
Girlfriend? Hey, I think you've
got heatstroke, you punk.

37:33.918 --> 37:35.378
SALES COMMISSION AGREEMENT

37:35.461 --> 37:39.924
Okay. I told you I didn't need a cut
of the proceeds.

37:42.635 --> 37:45.805
You know you're only receiving your
fair share, so don't worry.

37:46.639 --> 37:50.017
That's, uh, super weird way of thanking
someone, you know?

37:58.943 --> 38:00.528
-What?
-Shouldnt you get going?

38:00.611 --> 38:01.445
I was about to.

38:11.372 --> 38:16.252
What the? What's happening to me? I feel
dizzy?

38:19.630 --> 38:23.634
Hang on, wait. Okay. This is a real one.
Oh, what's happening? Oh, wait. Give me

38:23.718 --> 38:26.929
one second. Just a minute.

38:34.603 --> 38:35.438
Is this real?

38:35.521 --> 38:38.232
Ugh, I can barely even hold my head
up. In my bag, over there, there's

38:38.316 --> 38:40.526
a glucose solution. Could you get it for
me?

38:47.241 --> 38:50.619
Just, um, dump it all out and find
it for me, please? Hurry. Why is

38:50.703 --> 38:53.289
everything's spinning?

38:57.793 --> 39:02.506
Oh, I think that's it. That's it. I feel
like I might die.

39:06.677 --> 39:07.595
Oh, this is weird.

39:11.640 --> 39:12.475
Ow, my head.

39:15.227 --> 39:16.062
Get up.

39:16.812 --> 39:17.813
Oh my God.

39:19.899 --> 39:20.733
Thank you.

39:27.156 --> 39:29.575
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, just a moment.

39:32.870 --> 39:35.331
Why do you keep overworking your body
like this?

39:36.415 --> 39:37.249
Uh, do I?

39:37.333 --> 39:41.295
You didn't even treat your injury.
And you worked so hard you fainted.

39:42.838 --> 39:47.927
Your right. Whose fault do you think
that is though?

39:50.971 --> 39:54.100
No matter what you do, nothing's
gonna change my mind. So stop

39:54.183 --> 39:56.394
wasting your time.

40:00.064 --> 40:05.111
Be nice to the patient, I'm sick. Even if
it's valid, it's still a beatdown.

40:08.572 --> 40:12.201
Oh, God. I'll rest on the couch for a bit
before I go. I just can't move

40:12.284 --> 40:15.871
right now. Just for a moment.

40:17.706 --> 40:18.541
Hold on.

40:22.336 --> 40:23.587
Stay right where you are.

40:33.973 --> 40:34.807
Why?

40:41.147 --> 40:42.314
You'll wrinkle the rug.

40:54.368 --> 40:58.164
Oh my God. Why is it so far away?
I'm gonna die.

41:03.836 --> 41:05.629
I'll just stay here.

41:44.919 --> 41:49.173
Ow, my poor head. I told you I have a
headache.

41:51.342 --> 41:57.056
Ow, my head. Ugh, come on. Such a
strange man.

42:39.139 --> 42:41.475
What the hell? Where are my clothes?

42:57.825 --> 42:58.659
What?

43:02.788 --> 43:04.081
What, really? Come on.

43:07.626 --> 43:08.460
Please back up.

43:15.301 --> 43:16.260
Damn it!

43:22.057 --> 43:23.601
I'm busy, all right?

43:25.853 --> 43:27.271
What is he doing? What?

43:38.699 --> 43:43.245
Excuse me! Please let me through! Can you
reverse your tractor?

43:57.593 --> 44:00.679
What are you doing? Come on, move your
car!

44:01.889 --> 44:05.976
You must not be from around here. You're
driving on a one-way road.

44:08.479 --> 44:12.399
There's no such thing as a one way road
out here. I have the right of way.

44:12.483 --> 44:17.821
Oh. Come on. This road is for
exiting only!

44:25.663 --> 44:29.291
He's got crazy eyes. Sure, I'll back up.
Fine by me.

44:34.546 --> 44:40.636
What? Damn it! I'm stuck, damn it! Wait.
Hold on.

44:44.098 --> 44:44.932
Oh, no.

44:50.062 --> 44:53.565
Ugh, I gotta pull it out. Oh, great,
crazy bastard's coming over here.

44:53.649 --> 44:56.527
Come on, come on. Come on.

44:57.611 --> 44:59.446
I'm really trying to back up.

45:05.828 --> 45:10.749
Where's he going? What? What? What is he
doing? What?

45:45.826 --> 45:49.288
I'll back it up for you. Go on home.

46:04.303 --> 46:09.808
What is that bastard's deal? Come on,
are you crazy. Get it together.

46:38.003 --> 46:39.254
How are you getting home?

46:40.297 --> 46:41.215
I'll take the car.

46:41.715 --> 46:44.635
After all of that, you're putting
yourself behind the wheel?

46:44.718 --> 46:48.013
Oh, wow, I'm so touched. Are you worried?
Well, if you're that worried, then

46:48.096 --> 46:53.477
why don't you take just one look at those
documents I left. Thank you.

47:01.693 --> 47:06.824
Seriously, what the heck? Who is that?
Stop it! Who is that? Come on.

47:10.619 --> 47:13.038
-Let's get outta here.
-He's gonna pay for this.

47:32.307 --> 47:34.893
I can sell and essence even better
than corn.

47:43.151 --> 47:47.072
That guy from earlier, that was him,
wasn't it? The owner of Gojeuneok.

47:49.575 --> 47:51.451
I shouldn't have been so mean to him.

47:51.952 --> 47:52.786
Why?

47:54.746 --> 47:57.499
How could he work someone so hard they
get heatstroke? Not even a dog is

47:57.583 --> 48:01.044
treated like that. It's so damn rude.

48:01.128 --> 48:02.462
He's really not like that.

48:07.134 --> 48:08.093
What's going on?

48:09.928 --> 48:10.762
Nothing.

48:16.351 --> 48:18.437
Dam Ye-jin, go get some rest.

48:18.520 --> 48:20.689
-All right, sure.
-I mean, don't do anything stupid.

48:20.772 --> 48:23.108
I said I heard you. Now, go. Get outta
here.

48:23.609 --> 48:25.444
-See ya.
-Drive safe.

48:31.408 --> 48:32.451
I'm so tired.

48:36.914 --> 48:41.585
Ye-jin. Don't do this. This is no
time to act this way.

48:44.087 --> 48:45.797
I'm going to need a transfusion.

48:50.761 --> 48:52.512
I called about an order for a pickup.

48:52.596 --> 48:53.472
Just a moment.

48:53.555 --> 48:54.598
Okay.

48:57.351 --> 48:59.353
Okay. Let's see…

49:00.103 --> 49:01.063
Here are your drinks.

49:01.146 --> 49:01.980
Ah, great.

49:03.607 --> 49:06.151
-Thanks so much.
-Thank you. Have a nice night.

49:09.821 --> 49:13.450
Merci. This is trustworthy coffee, right?

49:13.533 --> 49:16.912
Dam Ye-Jin, herself, is a regular at
the café it came from.

49:17.454 --> 49:18.705
Dam Ye-jin, you said?

49:18.789 --> 49:21.208
Yeah. She's down there having coffee.
Right now.

49:22.918 --> 49:26.338
Really? The café? Uh, you should go
ahead and clock out. This coffee

49:26.421 --> 49:30.008
smells so good that I don't feel like
working.

49:31.176 --> 49:34.137
You've been working so hard all this time
with practically no break. Go sleep,

49:34.221 --> 49:35.681
and get some rest, and start tomorrow…

49:35.764 --> 49:36.598
Yeah, I really have.

49:36.682 --> 49:39.601
I'm gonna sleep tight. Ah, okay, okay.
Go home. Yes, okay, okay. Au revoir,

49:39.685 --> 49:41.311
au revoir. All right, all right.
Okay, now.

49:41.395 --> 49:42.354
With a new attitude.

49:42.437 --> 49:45.065
If you press down on your foot before you
go to bed.

50:08.088 --> 50:09.589
Didn't expect to see you here.

50:10.465 --> 50:13.552
Huh? Oh, Mr. Seo! You here for coffee?

50:14.052 --> 50:16.430
I'm actually here to work.

50:17.514 --> 50:20.892
Well, I'd go for the espresso. It's
definitely a ten out of ten.

50:21.810 --> 50:22.769
I'll give it a try.

51:29.544 --> 51:31.922
Super. Merci la pluie.

51:58.907 --> 52:03.078
Don't you have an umbrella? Or should I
save you for a change?

52:14.881 --> 52:17.092
This umbrella it's thee umbrella, right?

52:17.592 --> 52:21.096
Yep. This item gave me the thrill of my
very first sell-out. When it's

52:21.179 --> 52:24.808
raining, take a look around you.
I bet you'll see at least one of these.

52:24.891 --> 52:27.352
Oh, do you see that?

52:29.020 --> 52:32.023
If you're doing this well, I think you
should at least treat me to a

52:32.107 --> 52:34.734
-nice dinner.
-All right. Whenever you have the time to.

52:34.818 --> 52:35.652
Tonight.

52:37.821 --> 52:39.364
Treat me to a meal tonight.

52:41.575 --> 52:42.784
What are you hungry for?

52:43.493 --> 52:46.413
Hmm. How about a croissant?

52:51.251 --> 52:52.085
Ah, Mr. Seo.

52:54.337 --> 52:57.632
I don't date anyone that I have
business with. Um, I've found when

52:57.716 --> 53:02.971
emotions get involved, I end up losing
both the person and the work.

53:07.350 --> 53:11.354
I understand. Let's work, then. But once
the work is done, then let's eat a meal

53:11.438 --> 53:12.689
somewhere.

53:39.257 --> 53:41.134
Ugh, I can barely even hold my head up.

53:41.218 --> 53:42.052
Just…

53:42.135 --> 53:44.304
Dump it all out and find it for me,
please.

53:45.472 --> 53:48.350
DO NOT OVERDOSE: TAKE WHEN NECESSARY
MAY CAUSE DIZZINESS

54:06.326 --> 54:07.160
Thank you.

54:11.873 --> 54:17.462
Rose, you've really been through it.
I'll treat you well from now on.

54:23.051 --> 54:23.885
Hello.

54:26.054 --> 54:27.097
Oh, Mechoori?

54:30.767 --> 54:32.519
What? My meds?

54:36.356 --> 54:38.191
God, you're right. I'll be right there.

54:38.275 --> 54:39.526
It's too late now.

54:40.026 --> 54:41.987
-Tomorrow.
-No, I'll head over now.

54:42.070 --> 54:43.488
Do you know what time it is?

54:44.197 --> 54:46.116
It doesn't matter. Without those meds…

54:49.035 --> 54:51.663
Okay. Let's meet in the middle, then.

55:00.213 --> 55:02.382
Thanks for the phone. Get some rest.

55:04.301 --> 55:05.302
What was that about?

55:09.931 --> 55:13.351
You think I don't know it? The sound
of that rock rattling around in

55:13.435 --> 55:17.147
your heart? Mechoori, not even the fierce
cutting winds of winter can stop

55:17.230 --> 55:21.234
the spring breeze. No matter what, you'll
never stop it from forcing its way in.

55:21.318 --> 55:23.903
You know what I mean.

55:41.713 --> 55:43.089
HIT HOME SHOPPING

55:43.173 --> 55:46.009
PRESCRIPTION DRUG

56:00.774 --> 56:01.608
Yes, hello?

56:01.691 --> 56:05.487
Hey, Mechoori! There's an emergency.
Get to the farm right away!

56:09.157 --> 56:12.452
Hey, Mechoori, Mechoori. It's bad,
really bad.

56:15.080 --> 56:15.914
What happened?

56:15.997 --> 56:19.084
I was passing by and heard a noise so I
checked it out and found this whole area

56:19.167 --> 56:22.128
drenched in water. I think there's a
problem with the humidity controls. What

56:22.212 --> 56:23.046
should we do?

56:25.131 --> 56:28.343
We need to clean it off quickly.
If we don't move fast, then the wood

56:28.426 --> 56:31.012
will rot. Okay, I'm gonna get
the pressure sprayer.

56:33.515 --> 56:35.892
DEOKCHEON REST AREA

56:47.320 --> 56:48.905
I guess I'm the first one here.

56:58.498 --> 56:59.499
Oh, I'm sorry.

57:29.863 --> 57:33.199
Oh, where-- Where are they?

57:36.828 --> 57:37.954
We have to save these.

57:45.587 --> 57:46.504
What should I do?

57:51.009 --> 57:53.887
I'm such an idiot. Such an idiot.

58:24.626 --> 58:29.172
Song-mi. I guess I'll have to call
you back.

58:29.255 --> 58:31.341
PRODUCER EOM TEMPER

58:34.719 --> 58:35.553
Really.

58:52.529 --> 58:53.780
Where is he?

59:32.652 --> 59:34.779
Mom said she was coming.

59:35.363 --> 59:36.364
She'll be here soon.

59:43.079 --> 59:43.913
It's okay.

59:46.749 --> 59:47.584
It's okay.

59:52.338 --> 59:57.635
Mom said she was coming. She'll be
here soon.

59:57.719 --> 59:59.178
It's okay. It's okay.

59:59.262 --> 01:00:00.513
She'll be here soon.

01:00:02.390 --> 01:00:03.474
She'll be here soon.

01:00:10.315 --> 01:00:11.190
It's okay.

01:00:13.818 --> 01:00:18.781
It's okay. It's okay, Ye-jin. It's okay.

01:00:31.419 --> 01:00:32.253
Dam Ye-jin!

01:00:48.853 --> 01:00:49.687
I'm sorry.

01:02:20.820 --> 01:02:23.781
About earlier, that was…

01:02:25.992 --> 01:02:27.577
Just something that happened.

01:02:32.540 --> 01:02:33.374
I'm sorry I was late.

01:02:33.458 --> 01:02:34.500
You should be!

01:02:35.001 --> 01:02:36.711
Do you know what time it is now?

01:02:36.794 --> 01:02:38.880
I mean, I meant to be here earlier, but…

01:02:38.963 --> 01:02:41.382
Save it. Just give me my meds.

01:02:56.147 --> 01:02:56.981
Is this a joke?

01:02:58.733 --> 01:02:59.942
I'll give you one a day.

01:03:02.945 --> 01:03:04.071
What exactly are you doing?

01:03:04.155 --> 01:03:04.989
Dam Ye-jin.

01:03:07.992 --> 01:03:09.577
Let's see each other every day.

01:03:15.958 --> 01:03:19.712
Mom. I went to this place called Deokpung
Village. And there's this strange

01:03:19.796 --> 01:03:24.383
guy I met there. He's really uptight.

01:03:30.515 --> 01:03:34.852
And he keeps cutting me off, uh, before I
finished.

01:03:37.855 --> 01:03:39.565
But do you know what?

01:03:41.776 --> 01:03:48.699
Whenever I'm around him, I just feel
like everything's gonna be okay.

01:03:54.539 --> 01:03:55.581
So, I was wondering…

01:03:58.084 --> 01:04:02.171
Do I trust him instead of myself?

01:04:05.049 --> 01:04:07.009
And try all over again?

01:04:33.369 --> 01:04:36.873
Not even the fierce cutting winds
of winter can stop the spring breeze.

01:04:36.956 --> 01:04:43.921
No matter what, you'll never stop it from
forcing its way in.

01:04:54.765 --> 01:04:58.561
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05:13.951 --> 01:05:17.163
SUPER SWEET STEAMED CORN, RAW CORN
NATIONWIDE DELIVERY AVAILABLE

01:05:28.758 --> 01:05:30.760
So, did you spend the night with Ye-jin?

01:05:31.260 --> 01:05:33.638
I must be out of my mind. I must be
out of my mind.

01:05:33.721 --> 01:05:37.141
They'll contact you too, Ye-jin.
When they do, make sure to let me know.

01:05:37.224 --> 01:05:39.352
Contract renewal? You want to renew it?!

01:05:40.269 --> 01:05:44.023
Stop it, right now. I won't let you ruin
any other lives besides mine.

01:05:45.024 --> 01:05:47.151
Would you consider working for L'Etoile?

01:05:47.234 --> 01:05:50.071
Mr. Seo, you can just think of it as
giving me a tour of the raw materials

01:05:50.154 --> 01:05:51.072
farm. Oh, Mr. Seo.

01:05:51.864 --> 01:05:53.824
This will be the first and last
photoshoot.

01:05:53.908 --> 01:05:56.118
Then you should've turned it down.
Why'd you agree?

01:05:56.202 --> 01:05:57.578
Because of Ms. Dam Ye-jin.
